==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dead-eye
<hw>Dead"-eye`</hw> <pr>(d⟦ecr⟧d"⟦imac⟧`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A round, flattish, wooden block, encircled by a
rope, or an iron band, and pierced with three holes to receive the
lanyard; -- used to extend the shrouds and stays, and for other
purposes. Called also <altname>deadman's eye</altname>.</def>
<rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deadhead</ent>⟦br⟧
